PSNR(Peak signal-to-noise ratio: ) MSE(Mean Squared Error: )

$MSE = \frac{1}{n} \Sigma^{n}_{i=1} (Y_i - \hat{Y_i} )^2$

$PSNR = 10 \times \log_{10} \frac{MAX_I^2}{MSE} = 20 \times \log_{10} \frac{MAX_I}{\sqrt{MSE}}$

In [7]:
def mse(ref, dis):
    assert ref.shape == dis.shape, "Input images must have the same dimensions."
    d = ref.astype(np.float64) - dis.astype(np.float64)
    return np.mean(d **2)

print(f"MSE {mse(grayscale_array, grayscale_array):.03f}")
print(f"MSE {mse(grayscale_array, grayscale_blockiness_array):.03f}")
print(f"MSE {mse(grayscale_array, grayscale_blur_array):.03f}")

MSE 0.000
MSE 245.287
MSE 312.883

In [8]:
def psnr(ref, dis):
    assert ref.shape == dis.shape, "Input images must have the same dimensions."
    pixel_max = 255
    return 20 * math.log10(pixel_max / math.sqrt(mse(ref, dis)))

print(f"PSNR {psnr(grayscale_array, grayscale_blockiness_array):.03f}")
print(f"PSNR {psnr(grayscale_array, grayscale_blur_array):.03f}")

PSNR 24.234
PSNR 23.177
